list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment:
Added a safe way (I think) to ensure the track cover art and audio features update whenever a new song plays. I still need to update this when the user is in the UserStatistcs activity.
Fixed the error where the wrong stats would show if a user clicked to fast on the next activity and also the stuck activity where it would just display loading on the UI for the track audio features.
Lastly, I was able to get the current playing artist profile picture to show up on the homescreen whenever the song changes and a new artist is present.
Future improvement: Make all the above things mentioned faster.

task.summary: Default task
First understanding of working with JSON to eventually pull from Spotify API
Successfully gets album details from Spotify API using the wrapper and then updates the TextView (R.id.albumName) to the release date.
Successfully gets album details from Spotify API using the wrapper and then updates the TextView (R.id.albumName) to the release date.

Able to access private user data! Needed to update the scopes in the authentication array.
Need to structuring data and start working on UI now.
Finally able to access and store all of user's song data! If I ever need a reference, refer back to this code and method: getMySavedTracks() call.
Finally able to access and store all of user's song data! If I ever need a reference, refer back to this code and method: getMySavedTracks() call.
Implemented method to get user's top tracks from a year ago. Will use this data to display one's mood.
Cleaned up MainActivity. Did not need to use AppRemote since this app does not need it.

Working on the getTrackAudioFeatures() method. It correctly gets the acousticness of each song from the user's top tracks and adds them together. Then it takes the average and that will be the value used to help determine the color of the picture.
Got all audio features for top tracks and averages for each relevant variable for the UI.

The overlay() method seems to be working as intended. Now all that is left is to pass the user's input on how they perceive each color to represent the moods. Also, the colors seem a bit hash when comparing it to the original picture. I need to find a better way of masking color so the picture doesn't look totally different.
Layouts, changed layout for each activity.

App successfully works painting th picturte based on user top song meta data. To further the project, implement a way where the user's data is immediately ready to go from launching the application instead of waiting. I have some ideas about how to do this such as implementing a splash screen to retrieve the data at the start
Last, I need to make the app look somewhat presentable. I need to use some software to create a nice user interface. That is not a priority yet however.
Overall, this commit seems pretty hopeful and stable.
Latewr down the road can the integration with an LED strip come into the environment since there is meta data on each track (audio analysis) that may be helpful in lighting up a strip. (This is a long message)

Added scope to get current song being played.
Added method to get currently playing song
Added button to fetch this data

Added a couple of methods to get the song's audio analysis
Next is to store that analysis and start figuring out a way to display the data in a colorful way(maybe by pitch??)
Added functionality to populate a list that will hold songs that were added year(s) ago from the current date.
Able to display current playing song's cover art!
Got the basic UI done for the current playing song and info on it
Added number placeholders where the values of each song will be populated.
Removed status bar
Got rid of app remote
Cleaned up and commented more code. Also changed app theme
I NEEDED APP REMOTE! Me being dumb forgot that the sdk is always in sync and already handles the update of cover art. A person on reddit reminded me of this, gold was given as a thank you :)
Not sure why I was getting a 401 unauthorized code for awhile there. But this build seems to be stable and work.
Having trouble updating the UI with the song features. It doesnt not update the array list outside of the thread in connected() and i cannot update it within the thread. More research is needed.

AsyncTask is working properly which updates the UI accordingly. This means as the song changes, so does the track feature ui elements array list. This provides a clean and simple way of updating the ui in the background which has eliminated ugly code using different thread techniques and has solved a few exception errors.
Now displays the Key as a string instead of an integer.
Improved UI to read the values easier
loudness now displays dB unit
loudness now displays dB unit
loudness now displays dB unit (ignore last push)
Added UI tempo units (BPM)
Made the cover art much larger to admire their beauty.
Cleaned up some code and variables that were not being utilized.
Changed login screen fit a login button
Gave the login page a video view to make it look nice and modern. The video is from a royalty free site but will mostly likely not be the final one shown as I want to make it myself.
VideoView stops mediaPlayer when app launches. There is a simple fix if the api >= 26, need to make a solution for when the user's phone is api < 26.

Added a rough Home Screen! It needs some work still, but is a great placeholder for now. I managed to get the current playing track to move onto the screen that was being displayed originally to show the track's audio features. In addition, one cannot go back to the login screen anymore which is what was needed.
Overall, I am happy with the progress I was able to make today.

Learned about different pixel densities. The correct pixel density image will be used to each corresponding phone and will utilize the the correct one across platforms.
Also, added more images to the UI to make it look a tad better. Still needs some love though.

Changed the app remote and spotify service activation to apply whenever the user leaves the login page and goes to the home screen. Also made a change where the coverart url is guarenteed to be the first element in the list. Last, I made it to where the user could not spam the back button when getting the current song (2.5s delay till button becomes active again).
This is to prevent the fetch from not completing (track audio features).

Added a safe way (I think) to ensure the track cover art and audio features update whenever a new song plays. I still need to update this when the user is in the UserStatistcs activity.
Fixed the error where the wrong stats would show if a user clicked to fast on the next activity and also the stuck activity where it would just display loading on the UI for the track audio features.
Lastly, I was able to get the current playing artist profile picture to show up on the homescreen whenever the song changes and a new artist is present.
Future improvement: Make all the above things mentioned faster.

Reworked how data is passed between activities. I now use an object (CurrentPlaying) to hold all the valid data between activities.
Also, I have figured out a way to update the UI faster between song changes and make sure nothing wonky happens.
Future implementations: - Update UI automatically from UserStatistics without having to go back. - Put profile picture fetch and cover art fetch in different async tasks or other methods. Right now if the same song is playing then the profile picture gets reset to the default picture as well as the artist picture.
